# .pii-patterns.example — template for the pre-commit PII blocklist.
#
# Copy to .pii-patterns (GIT-IGNORED) and replace the placeholders with YOUR OWN
# identifiers. The pre-commit hook (scripts/pre-commit) greps the staged diff
# against these — one POSIX extended regex per line, case-insensitive. '#'
# comments and blank lines are ignored.
#
# NEVER put real values in THIS file — it is committed. Real values go ONLY in
# .pii-patterns, which .gitignore keeps out of history. The whole point of the
# split is that the blocklist is itself sensitive: a list of your crown-jewel
# strings must never ship in the repo.
#
# Suggested categories (replace each RHS with your real string):
#   EMPLOYER_PAYROLL_STRING       # e.g. the exact text on your salary credits
#   FAMILY_SURNAME                # names that appear on family transfers
#   HOME_OR_FAMILY_PLACE_NAME     # a town/city that pins your location
#   LANDLORD_OR_MANAGEMENT_CO     # rent counterparty
#   ANY_ACCOUNT_LABEL_FRAGMENT    # a distinctive slice of an account number
